00:06:50,880 --> 00:06:52,401
[SPEAKER_15]: My name is Henry Rapa, Jr.

111
00:06:53,221 --> 00:06:58,283
[SPEAKER_15]: I'm counsel to Joseph Musi with respect to this request for a zoning variance.

112
00:06:58,764 --> 00:07:01,705
[SPEAKER_15]: Currently, the property has two parking spaces.

113
00:07:02,706 --> 00:07:03,986
[SPEAKER_15]: Zoning requires four.

114
00:07:04,927 --> 00:07:06,067
[SPEAKER_15]: So it's nonconforming.

115
00:07:07,368 --> 00:07:12,250
[SPEAKER_15]: The petitioner's plan will actually reduce that nonconformity by one spot.

116
00:07:12,831 --> 00:07:13,531
[SPEAKER_15]: So he'll have three

117
00:07:14,481 --> 00:07:19,902
[SPEAKER_15]: parking spaces on site.

118
00:07:23,723 --> 00:07:30,064
[SPEAKER_15]: His driveway is actually blocked in some aspects by people parking on the street.

119
00:07:30,624 --> 00:07:38,325
[SPEAKER_15]: One of the submissions in the package has a picture that shows a car parked in front of his driveway extending out.

120
00:07:39,205 --> 00:07:43,126
[SPEAKER_15]: So it actually becomes quite problematical for him to

121
00:07:44,720 --> 00:07:49,562
[SPEAKER_15]: access his driveway when people are parking beyond where the curb ends.

122
00:07:51,023 --> 00:07:54,884
[SPEAKER_15]: So he has nowhere else to park except in the front yard.

123
00:07:56,005 --> 00:07:59,486
[SPEAKER_15]: The property does not allow access to the backyard.

124
00:07:59,506 --> 00:08:06,029
[SPEAKER_15]: The house itself blocks that type of access to park anywhere other than the front.

125
00:08:07,369 --> 00:08:11,371
[SPEAKER_15]: And as you can see from the picture submitted,

126
00:08:12,453 --> 00:08:19,157
[SPEAKER_15]: It can be very challenging to get in and out of his driveway with that people parking beyond the curb cut.

127
00:08:19,978 --> 00:08:32,306
[SPEAKER_15]: So based on the circumstances, the four-prong test, we submit to be satisfied.

128
00:08:35,848 --> 00:08:40,431
[SPEAKER_15]: And we ask the members of the board to grant his request for relief

129
00:08:41,441 --> 00:08:42,422
[SPEAKER_15]: to park in the front yard.

130
