443
00:36:31,971 --> 00:36:37,576
[SPEAKER_00]: Specifically, we're looking for a variance for one section on the northwest section of the property.

444
00:36:38,477 --> 00:36:47,144
[SPEAKER_00]: Essentially, we're looking to accomplish two things with this fence is to improve security for our property and then also to enhance some of the privacy

445
00:36:48,612 --> 00:36:53,255
[SPEAKER_00]: The fence on the northwest side of our yard basically is on a very steep slope and gradient.

446
00:36:54,596 --> 00:37:03,981
[SPEAKER_00]: Our street is parallel to McCormick and because of the gradient and the slope, basically our neighbors on McCormick sort of have a direct view into our yard and also our home.

447
00:37:05,102 --> 00:37:08,704
[SPEAKER_00]: Additionally, we sit on a bit of a rock ledge and there's a safety issue.

448
00:37:08,724 --> 00:37:13,867
[SPEAKER_00]: There's approximately about like a four foot drop between our property and our neighbors on McCormick.

449
00:37:14,593 --> 00:37:17,255
[SPEAKER_00]: Um, so also looking to eliminate a bit of a safety concern.

450
00:37:17,275 --> 00:37:21,357
[SPEAKER_00]: There's quite a bit of overbrush and, um, you know, trees sort of growing in that area.

451
00:37:21,377 --> 00:37:25,019
[SPEAKER_00]: So looking to kind of seal that off in the yard to eliminate any safety concerns.

452
00:37:26,678 --> 00:37:35,543
[SPEAKER_00]: Additionally, from a security perspective, our neighbors to the north are the resources for human development, and we have a really great relationship with them.

453
00:37:36,063 --> 00:37:40,526
[SPEAKER_00]: They're a nonprofit that provides care for several developmentally disabled adults.

454
00:37:40,966 --> 00:37:48,170
[SPEAKER_00]: We've had a few instances where one of the residents has come in and basically into the yard without permission, has damaged some of our lighting.

455
00:37:48,850 --> 00:37:53,393
[SPEAKER_00]: So again, just looking for some enhanced security and privacy in constructing this fence.

456
00:37:54,853 --> 00:38:03,681
[SPEAKER_00]: Basically, again, in terms of the variance request, the idea behind the two-foot extension is to just give us a little bit more privacy and less visibility from the Cormac app.

