[SPEAKER_08]: I think that the alternative would be more detrimental to the neighborhood.

1402
02:15:40,179 --> 02:15:48,505
[SPEAKER_08]: And this is an important area on an important street, and I think that this is a proper enhancement of the property.

1403
02:15:50,041 --> 02:15:50,281
[SPEAKER_09]: Okay.

1404
02:15:51,242 --> 02:16:10,079
[SPEAKER_09]: And then, um, so if there's no other comments on those issues, so the last one is, um, the different, um, criteria for, uh, special permit for, um, for changes to a nonconforming building.

1405
02:16:10,179 --> 02:16:13,401
[SPEAKER_09]: And so here it is, um,

1406
02:16:17,582 --> 02:16:34,811
[SPEAKER_09]: uh, Board of Appeals may award a special permit to reconstruct, extend, alter, or change a non-conforming structure in accordance with this section only if it determines such reconstruction, extension, alteration, or change is not substantially more detrimental to the neighborhood than the existing non-conforming structure.

1407
02:16:35,272 --> 02:16:36,833
[SPEAKER_09]: So here we have an alteration

1408
02:16:37,949 --> 02:16:42,712
[SPEAKER_09]: to an existing structure with an existing side yard nonconformity.

1409
02:16:43,252 --> 02:16:49,496
[SPEAKER_09]: It does increase the nature of the nonconformity under the ordinance.

1410
02:16:52,337 --> 02:16:53,878
[SPEAKER_09]: The footprint has not changed.

1411
